	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>N.Y.</placeName> <date>Sunday</date>&#44; The</p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><date>2nd of Tammuz</date></p>
			<p rend="align(right)"><date>&#40;June&#41; 1866</date>.</p>
				<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
				<p>Greetings&#44; etc. to my<lb/> friend&#44; etc. <persName>Isaac</persName> son of <persName>Uri Leeser</persName>&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">After my greetings of peace&#44; I want<lb/> to ask you for one favor&#44; and I am<lb/> ready to pay for your trouble&#44; as<lb/> much as you will justly impose upon<lb/> me. God is my witness that it is not<lb/> for my own glory but for Him and his<lb/> Torah that I do this. There is a time<lb/> for silence and a time for speech.<lb/> We should not permit The final mish&#45;<lb/>nah of Chapter IX of the Treatise Sotah<lb/> to come true&#44; &#8220;The wisdom of the Scribes<lb/> grows stale&#44; and the righteous become<lb/> despised&#44; then truth is lacking.&#8221;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">It is now three days since an old<lb/> man died here and departed this life<lb/> from us and all <placeName>Israel</placeName>. His name was<lb/> <persName>Rabbi Isaac</persName>&#44; called <persName>Isaac Ha Kohen</persName>&#44;<lb/> a righteous and pious man as you will<lb/> see in the newspaper of <persName>Rev Isaac&#39;s</persName> of</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>last week. His son&#44; <persName>Mr. Cohen</persName>&#44; The<lb/> Parass of Rodaphei Zedek&#44; asked me<lb/> to pronounce an appropriate eulogy<lb/> for his father&#44; since I was a frequent<lb/> visitor to his house and a loyal<lb/> friend. I did as he told me and de&#45;<lb/>cided to pronounce the eulogy in<lb/> his home after he had been prepared<lb/> for burial&#44; because in that house he<lb/> used to sit and study for many years.<lb/> I uttered words that came from the<lb/> heart. Everyone wept for him and<lb/> every eye was moist with tears. But<lb/> I shall give you only a small portion<lb/> of it. I began with a quotation from<lb/> the Treatise &#8220;Mored<add>&#63;</add> Katan<add>&#63;</add>&#8221;.  &#40;The<lb/> quotation from the eulogy takes up &#189; <lb/> page. The point of it is that this old<lb/> man was very useful to the community<lb/> and was comparable to the sun at its<lb/> height. Hence this death is a universal<lb/> misfortune&#44; comparable to the setting of<lb/> the sun at midday&#41;. The letter then continues&#58;</p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p>But <persName>Rev. Issacs</persName> was evidently en&#45;<lb/>vious for he did not mention my name<lb/> in his newspaper. He did mention all<lb/> the mourners&#44; and who do you think<lb/> was at their head&#63; <persName>Rev. Isaacs</persName>.<lb/> That is why I ask you to do me a favor<lb/> and mention my name in the &#8220;Occident&#8221;<lb/> and I shall compensate you whatever<lb/> you say for mentioning my name in a<lb/> good sense. Also send me The &#8220;Occident&#8221;<lb/> and I will consider it an act of <lb/> righteousness. Everyone here is angry<lb/> that he neglected to mention my name.<lb/> I shall be forever indebted to you and<lb/> I hope to do something in return. For<lb/> truth must stand forever.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I also should like to have you<lb/> let me know what you did with the<lb/> Sefer Torah in which the first chapter<lb/> of the portion &#8220;Mi&#45;Ketz&#8221; &#40;Genesis&#44; 41&#41; is<lb/> missing&#44; and whether you corrected the<lb/> Sefer Torah. Has much correcting neces&#45;</p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p>sary as you wrote in your letter<lb/> when I was in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>&#44; and I<lb/> send greetings to my friend <persName>Mrs. Papfer</persName>.<lb/>  Now I want to tell you my good news that<lb/> my son in <placeName>Stalpe</placeName> in <placeName>Pomerania</placeName> became<lb/> engaged and the wedding will be very<lb/> soon with Mazel Tov.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Again I ask you not to be<lb/> angry at me.</p>
			<p rend="indent(6)"><persName role="author">Eliezar Phillips</persName></p>
			<p rend="indent(6)">&#40;Scribe in <placeName>N.Y.</placeName>&#41;</p>
				<p>If you want to honor me with a<lb/> few lines my address is<lb/> <persName>L. Phillips</persName>&#44; <placeName>203 Broome St.&#44; N.Y.</placeName></p>
			<pb n="5"/>
				<p><del><persName>MRS. SOLOMON GRAYZEL</persName><lb/> <placeName>THE SHELBURNE<lb/> 13TH STREET AND LINDLEY AVENUE<lb/> PHILADELPHIA&#44; PA.</placeName></del></p>
